dfischer.utils

Class HttpTestURL

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.HttpTestURL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    HttpTestURLSetExecutionStepInterface, java.lang.Runnable

    public class HttpTestURL
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable, HttpTestURLSetExecutionStepInterface
    Executes a HTTP request and receives the HTTP response .
    • Supports the HTTP methods POST and GET
    • Supports encrypted connections (HTTPS) - including PKCS#12 client certificate authentication
    • Supports NTLM authentication
    • Supports cookies over multiple calls
    • Supports HTTP V1.1 connection pools over multiple calls (keep-alive)
    • Supports URL calls through proxy servers
    • Supports receiving chunked data and receiving compressed data in a transparent way
    • Supports to specify a request timeout
    • Supports HTTP basic authorization and proxy-authorization
    • Measures performance details of the HTTP/S request
    • Collects all response data for further analysis
    Usage: create first a new instance and then call the method execute(). After that you can examine the received response.

    Measured performance data:

     <-dns resolve time-><-ssl handshake time-><-socket connect time-><-request transmit time-><-response header wait time-><-response header receive time-><-response content receive time->
 <-----------------------------------------------------------total time ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
    The TLS/SSL certificate chain verifier accepts all HTTPS server certificates, also if they are invalid.
    See Also:
    HttpLoadTest.httpResponseOk(HttpTestURL,int,int,String, String), PerformanceData.setPassed(int, HttpTestURL), PerformanceData.setFailed(int, String, HttpTestURL, LogVector), HttpSocketPool, CookieHandler
